properties.areaDesc: West Slopes South Central Cascades and Passes; West Slopes North Central Cascades and Passes; West Slopes North Cascades and Passes
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued December 31 at 1:36PM PST until January 2 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Rain will transition to snow during the day Wednesday
resulting in snow accumulations over the Cascades. Total snow
accumulations of 2 to 6 inches above 2000 feet, 8 to 14 inches
above 4000 feet, and 1 to 2 feet above 5000 feet. Locally higher
amounts possible above 6000 feet.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Whatcom, Skagit,
Snohomish, King, Pierce, and Lewis Counties, including the Mount
Baker Ski Area, Stevens Pass, Snoqualmie Pass, the Crystal
Mountain Ski Area, Paradise on Mount Rainier, and White Pass.

* WHEN...From 7 AM Wednesday to 4 AM PST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be difficult at times over the mountain
passes.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow levels will fall to around 4000 feet
late Wednesday morning, then to below 3000 feet by Wednesday
evening.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM WEDNESDAY TO 4 AM PST THURSDAY ABOVE 3000 FEET
